#Ingredients
* 1 pint cherry tomatoes, each one halved
* 1/2 tsp dried basil 
* 1/4 tsp dried oregano
* 1-2 cloves of garlic minced, or 1/2 tsp Penzey's dried minced garlic
* Approximately 3-4 tbsp of olive oil
* Optional: handful of baby spinach

#Instructions
* Using a wide pan or pot, pour in the olive oil and gently heat to medium-low heat.
* After oil is heated, add the cherry tomatoes. Ideally they will be spread out in an even layer.
* After about 5 minutes, add the dried spices. Decrease the heat to low.
* Stir occasionally for 15-20 minutes. When it is done, there should be oil but not a lot of water in the pan.
* If using, add baby spinach, allow to wilt for about 1 minute, then turn off heat
* In most cases, use a slotted spoon to serve

*This dish is tasty with bread, cheese, and serrano ham.
